Hello - I'm announcing something very special today... On May 19th i'll be taking over KOKO. People that know me, will know how much of a milestone this is. Not only cos it's an iconic venue in London, but because Camden is where i grew up. It's where i learnt to DJ some 20 years ago, and it's where my roots are.

The first time I went to this venue, it was called Camden Palace and they hosted under 18 garage raves. I was 14 and dressed up to the nines, ready with the gun fingers and lots of attitude. I'd just bought my decks around that time and was gassed to be going out hearing all the garage DJs and MCs. It was a scene so intrinsic to London and so many people were breaking through - think Ms. Dynamite, So Solid Crew, Heartless Crew. 

My school is just up the road, (s/o 'Camden School For Girls' where I first learnt how to DJ at an after School workshop ran by the youth organisation 'Bigga Fish') I would walk past this venue all the time in my teens after eating chicken nuggets at MC Donalds or having a hot chocolate at the Costa up the road. Never in a million years would I ever have thought all these years later I would be hosting my own event here. A real pinch myself moment!

I have such a sick line up of guests to announce soon..

Tickets go on sale on the 10th feb, sign up for pre-sale tix via my bio to get the link first 💞

xoxo

a few pics from last week when I took part in the #SaveTheNight2023 community panel at fabric. I was invited to share my thoughts alongside my peers @shaymalt @hannah_shogbola & @tashlc . we discussed ‘In this period of surging booking fees, how can promoters best be supported and find success?’ 

a topic that I think is more prevalent than ever with so many new djs on the circuit. the industry has become incredibly over saturated & it's hard for people to sustain a career. it's fair to say we were all in agreement that there should be transparecy from promoters, but ultimately djs need to be realistic about DJ fees and appreciatating they're part of an eco system and taking each gig as it comes. we discussed so much more but don't wanna write an essay on here lol

thank you to the peoples @fabriclondonofficial for having us & to @jagermeister & @resident_advisor for backing this. #SaveTheNight is a fund and mentorship scheme which will offer €100,000 in grants to innovative initiatives which will help make nightlife a better place. applications for the 2023 are now open!
 
more infos & application infos 👇🏻 www.jagermeister.com/en/save-the-night or via the link in my bio. 

#SaveTheNight #SavetheNightFund2023

Couldn't be happier to announce Amaliah - 'Manifold' is OUT TODAY 💕

We've been working on this for well over a year, maybe even two years. Lots of back and forth to make sure it was just right, but tbh from the moment I heard Amaliah's initial demos I knew I wanted to sign something from her (keep in mind she'd only been producing for a few months!)

Amaliah continues to impress me and i feel in awe of her talent. She's a real natural and one of the most humble people i've met. I feel so privileged to be putting out her debut release, as i know this is just the beginning of something really special 🤍 she's just at the beginning of her production journey and boy there is so much more incredible music to come!!

People take note, @amaliahppeche is only just getting started 🔥🔥🔥
